desc:
(@MinUnits@) Riftwalkers open a gap between dimensions and summon their ally Zac, who grows in power based on the total star level of Riftwalkers.

Zac gains the last-listed Trait of the closest Riftwalker.
name: Riftwalker

desc:
A.D.M.I.N. programs a custom configuration per player each game.

(@MinUnits@) [Initialize ADMIN cause and effect]
(@MinUnits@) [Add another effect to the program]. Boost all tiers by @4Tooltip@%
(@MinUnits@) Boost previous tiers by @6Tooltip@%
name: A.D.M.I.N.

desc:
Anima Squad members pose after champion kills, increasing their fame. Each point of fame grants @HealthPerStack@ permanent Health to each Anima Squad member.

They also gain:
(@MinUnits@) @InitialAD@% Attack Damage and @InitialAP@ Ability Power

Total fame: @TFTUnitProperty.trait:TFT8_AnimaFameStacks@
Bonus Health: @TFTUnitProperty.trait:TFT8_AnimaFameHP@
name: Anima Squad

desc:
When a LaserCorp drone pilot attacks or is hit by an attack, their combat drone deals magic damage to the agent's target (@ICD@ second cooldown).

When a unit with a drone dies, the drone is reassigned to another unit with a drone.

Drone lasers deal:
(@MinUnits@) @MagicDamage@ magic damage
(@MinUnits@) @MagicDamage@ magic damage
(@MinUnits@) @MagicDamage@ magic damage. All champions get a LaserCorp drone.
(@MinUnits@) @MagicDamage@ magic damage. All champions get a LaserCorp drone.

Drone damage last round: @TFTUnitProperty.trait:TFT8_Lasercorps_DamageTRAKey@ magic damage
name: LaserCorps

desc:
Brawlers gain additional maximum Health.

(@MinUnits@) +@BonusPercentHealth*100@% maximum Health
name: Brawler

desc:
Use the Mecha selector item to choose a PRIME.

Combat start: The PRIME combines with the 2 nearest Mecha, absorbing @HealthPercent@% of their Base Health.

(@MinUnits@) The PRIME gains @APAmount@ Ability Power and @ADPercent@% Attack Damage
(@MinUnits@) All Mechas gain @APAmount@ Ability Power and @ADPercent@% Attack Damage; the PRIME gains double this amount
name: Mecha:PRIME

desc: Threats do not have a Trait bonus, but instead have powerful Abilities and increased base stats.
name: Threat

desc:
After every 2 damaging ability projectiles, Quickdraw units fire a bonus ability projectile. Bonus shots deal:

(@MinUnits@) @DamageModifier*100@% total damage.
(@MinUnits@) @DamageModifier*100@% total damage.
(@MinUnits@) @DamageModifier*100@% total damage.
name: Quickdraw

desc:
Your team heals a percentage of their maximum Health every @Seconds@ seconds, and Mascots heal double the amount.

When Mascots die, they retreat to the sidelines to cheer on your team. Your team's healing increases by @HealthRegenPerMascot@% for each cheering Mascot.

(@MinUnits@) @BaseHealthRegen@% healing
name: Mascot

desc: Depending on the weather, The Forecaster grants a different bonus to adjacent allies. The weather changes every game.
name: Forecaster

desc:
This Trait is active only when you have exactly 1 or 4 unique Aces.

(@MinUnits@) Execute enemies under @ExecuteThreshhold@% Health
name: Ace

desc:
Innate: Increased movement speed.

Duelists' attacks grant bonus Attack Speed, up to @MaxStacks@ stacks.

(@MinUnits@) +@ASPerStack@% Attack Speed per stack
(@MinUnits@) +@ASPerStack@% Attack Speed per stack
(@MinUnits@) +@ASPerStack@% Attack Speed per stack; Duelists take @DRPercent@% less damage
(@MinUnits@) +@ASPerStack@% Attack Speed per stack; Duelists take @DRPercent@% less damage
name: Duelist

desc:
(@MinUnits@) Ezreal learns from his older, more handsome self and joins him in future adventures.

Ezreal's Ability becomes a blast that hits all enemies in a line.

Ultimate Ezreal's Ability summons one additional temporal duplicate.
name: Parallel

desc:
Ox Force units gain bonus defenses. Once per combat, when they would drop below one health, they instead go to one health and become immune to damage for @Seconds@ second.

(@MinUnits@) @Defenses@ Armor and Magic Resist
name: Ox Force

desc:
Your team gains bonus Magic Resist, and Aegis units gain more.

(@MinUnits@) +@MagicResist@ Magic Resist, +@AegisMagicResist@ for Aegis
name: Aegis

desc:
The Underground must sneak through the sewers after each player combat and crack @RoundCount@ locks to open a vault. When the vault opens, you may choose to take the loot now, or attempt another heist for even better rewards.

(@MinUnits@) @WinProgress@ locks per win, @LossProgress@ per loss

Current Heist Level: @TFTUnitProperty.trait:TFT8_Underground_CurrentStage@
name: Underground

desc:
Star Guardians gain more Mana in combat.

(@MinUnits@) @AdditionalManaPercentage@% Mana
name: Star Guardian

desc:
(@MinUnits@) Once per combat at @HealthThreshold@% Health, Pranksters spawn a target dummy, move to a safe location, and restore @HealthRegen@ Health.
(@MinUnits@) And, Prankster dummies stun the enemy that killed them for @StunDuration@ seconds.
(@MinUnits@) The Health restore is increased to @HealthRegen@ Health and the stun duration becomes @StunDuration@ seconds.
name: Prankster

desc:
The InfiniTeam opens a portal to an alternate timeline. At the start of combat, any InfiniTeam unit placed on a portal summons an alternate version of themself with different items. They get 1 for each Augment you own.

The copies have reduced Health and damage.

(@MinUnits@) @NumberOfPortals@ portal opens, @DamageReduction@% damage and @PercentHealth@% HP
(@MinUnits@) @NumberOfPortals@ portals open, @DamageReduction@% damage and @PercentHealth@% HP
(@MinUnits@) @NumberOfPortals@ portals open, @DamageReduction@% damage and @PercentHealth@% HP
name: InfiniTeam

desc:
When Heart units cast their Ability, your team gains stacking Ability Power for the rest of combat.

(@MinUnits@) +@APPerCast@ Ability Power
name: Heart

desc:
(@MinUnits@) Combat start: Lie dormant while absorbing the souls of allies that die. Gain @BonusAP@ Ability Power for each soul.

Once per combat at @HealthThreshold@% Health (or when your team has died), come alive and fight.
name: Corrupted

desc:
(@MinUnits@) Combat start: Strike a pose that grants your team @BaseBonusDamage@% bonus damage, which increases by @BonusDamagePer3Star@% for every 3-star champion on your team.

Bonus damage: @TFTUnitProperty.trait:TFT8_Supers_TotalBonusDamage@%
name: Supers

desc:
Renegade units deal bonus damage, and the last one standing deals more.

(@MinUnits@) @BasePercentBonusDamage@% bonus damage, extra @AdditionalBonusDamage@% for last alive
name: Renegade

desc:
Every @RefreshSeconds@ seconds, Spellslinger's next attack instead fires a magic orb at a random target, which explodes for @MagicDamage@% Ability Power as magic damage.

Spellslingers gain:
(@MinUnits@) +@AP@ Ability Power
(@MinUnits@) +@AP@ Ability Power
(@MinUnits@) +@AP@ Ability Power
(@MinUnits@) +@AP@ Ability Power, and orbs deal @MagicDamage@% Ability Power
name: Spellslinger

desc:
Combat start: Sureshots gain bonus Attack Damage now, and every @Frequency@ seconds.

(@MinUnits@) +@BonusAD*100@% Attack Damage
name: Sureshot

desc:
Your team gains bonus Armor, and Defenders gain more.

(@MinUnits@) +@BonusArmor@ Armor, +@DefenderBonusArmor@ for Defenders
name: Defender

desc:
Each round, Gadgeteens create random modified weapons with powerful effects that fall apart after one round. Gadgeteens also gain Damage and Damage Reduction for each item equipped to them.

(@MinUnits@) Create @ItemsToMake@ item, @Itembuff@% per item.
(@MinUnits@) Create @ItemsToMake@ items, @Itembuff@% per item.
name: Gadgeteen

desc:
Hackers gain Omnivamp and summon a H4ckerr!m. Any unit placed in the rider hex will be sent to the enemy backline and is untargetable for the first @SecondsUntargetable@ seconds of combat.

(@MinUnits@) +@Omnivamp*100@% Omnivamp
(@MinUnits@) +@Omnivamp*100@% Omnivamp for Hackers, +@Horsevamp*100@% for the rider
(@MinUnits@) +@Omnivamp*100@% Omnivamp for Hackers, +@Horsevamp*100@% for the rider
(@MinUnits@) +@Omnivamp*100@% Omnivamp for Hackers, +@Horsevamp*100@% for the rider

Omnivamp: heal for some of damage dealt
name: Hacker
